WEBVTT

01:02.275 --> 01:04.027
I don't know the right words.

01:06.613 --> 01:08.156
Ought to be a septon here.

01:14.913 --> 01:16.288
You were a true knight.

01:18.416 --> 01:20.168
You never beat me
when I didn't deserve it.

01:21.419 --> 01:22.419
Fuck.

01:23.922 --> 01:25.757
Except that time in Maidenpool.

01:29.094 --> 01:31.179
It was the inn boy
ate the widow woman's pie.

01:32.931 --> 01:35.183
Not me. I told you.

01:36.142 --> 01:37.268
Why, you...

01:44.234 --> 01:45.693
Doesn't matter now.

02:02.293 --> 02:04.003
I'd leave your sword, but it...

02:04.629 --> 02:06.256
it would only rust in the ground.

02:12.679 --> 02:14.430
I wish you didn't die, ser.

02:20.770 --> 02:22.605
I'll take good care of the horses.

02:37.661 --> 02:40.415
Eat like a king if I sold you three.

02:42.458 --> 02:44.209
For a year or two.

02:45.628 --> 02:46.754
Then what?

02:51.467 --> 02:54.220
That road ends in outlawry or beggary.

03:04.314 --> 03:05.982
We could go to a city.

03:09.485 --> 03:11.654
King's Landing? Lannisport?

03:25.834 --> 03:27.045
Could join the City Watch.

03:32.675 --> 03:34.177
Stop raping, ser.

03:45.438 --> 03:47.565
Fits my grip as well as it ever fit his.

03:53.112 --> 03:54.989
And there is a tourney at Ashford Meadow.

05:27.457 --> 05:29.834
Hello there.
Are you the stableboy?

05:34.672 --> 05:37.133
I want the palfrey rubbed down.

05:37.216 --> 05:39.635
And oats for all three. You tend to them?

05:39.719 --> 05:42.555
I could, if I wanted.

05:42.638 --> 05:44.515
None of that. See to the horses.

05:44.599 --> 05:47.060
You'll get a copper if you do well,
and a clout in the ear if not.

05:58.654 --> 05:59.655
Sit where you like.

06:12.043 --> 06:14.087
There's good lamb
roasted with a crust of herbs

06:14.170 --> 06:16.714
and some ducks my son shot down.
Which will you have?

06:18.049 --> 06:19.092
Both.

06:21.386 --> 06:22.929
You're big enough for it.

06:34.357 --> 06:36.692
-How much farther to Ashford?
-Day's ride.

06:39.028 --> 06:41.364
Is my boy seeing to your horses
or has he run off again?

06:43.032 --> 06:44.033
No, he's there.

06:44.117 --> 06:45.827
Half the town's gone down the tourney.

06:45.910 --> 06:47.537
Mine would, too, if I allowed it.

06:48.454 --> 06:49.705
I swear, I couldn't tell you why.

06:49.789 --> 06:51.999
Knights are built the same as other men.

06:53.042 --> 06:55.753
And I never knew a joust
to change the price of eggs.

06:58.506 --> 07:00.591
Bound for the tourney yourself?

07:00.675 --> 07:02.093
I dreamed of you.

07:09.016 --> 07:11.727
Stay the fuck away from me. You hear?

07:13.312 --> 07:14.355
My lord?

07:38.212 --> 07:39.630
Never you mind that one, ser.

07:39.714 --> 07:41.174
I'll see about your food.

07:49.432 --> 07:53.186
Hiya! Take that! Yah!

07:56.981 --> 07:57.982
Oi!

07:58.483 --> 07:59.484
My lord.

07:59.984 --> 08:02.612
-You thief!
-I did not mean to offend you.

08:02.695 --> 08:05.072
Take that armor off you. Now!

08:05.156 --> 08:08.618
And be glad Thunder didn't kick you
in that fool head of yours.

08:08.701 --> 08:10.453
He's a war horse, not a boy's pony.

08:10.536 --> 08:12.246
I could ride him as well as you.

08:12.997 --> 08:14.499
Close your insolent mouth.

08:15.166 --> 08:16.167
I--

08:16.501 --> 08:18.461
I'm a knight, I'll have you know.

08:18.544 --> 08:20.212
You don't look to be a knight.

08:21.297 --> 08:24.217
-What, all knights look the same, do they?
-No.

08:24.300 --> 08:26.177
But they don't look like you either.

08:27.512 --> 08:28.596
Your belt's made of rope.

08:29.972 --> 08:32.475
So long as it holds
my scabbard, it serves.

08:32.558 --> 08:35.937
Are you going to the tourney, then?
Do you mean to enter the lists?

08:36.938 --> 08:38.231
Yeah, I suppose I do.

08:38.856 --> 08:41.234
Take me with you, ser. Please.

08:41.317 --> 08:43.068
And what might your mother say to that?

08:43.152 --> 08:44.445
Not much.

08:44.529 --> 08:45.863
She's dead.

08:46.447 --> 08:47.823
Is the innkeeper not your...

08:50.618 --> 08:51.994
You're an orphan boy.

08:52.078 --> 08:53.079
Are you?

08:54.539 --> 08:57.083
I was. Once.

08:57.833 --> 08:59.293
Till my ser took me in.

09:00.920 --> 09:02.713
Taught me arms and riding, and...

09:04.257 --> 09:06.384
and taught me everything, really.

09:07.593 --> 09:09.428
Best he could.

09:09.512 --> 09:13.140
If you could bring me to Ashford,
I could squire for you, ser.

09:13.224 --> 09:15.893
And you can teach me best you can.

09:15.977 --> 09:18.062
No, I have no need for a squire, lad.

09:18.145 --> 09:19.855
Every knight needs a squire.

09:19.939 --> 09:22.692
And you look like you need one
more than most.

09:25.403 --> 09:27.363
And you look like you need
a good clout in the ear.

09:28.739 --> 09:29.949
Fill me a sack of oats.

09:30.032 --> 09:32.243
I'm off for Ashford. Alone.

09:38.416 --> 09:40.751
Look, lad, I promise you...

09:41.836 --> 09:44.170
you're better off not squiring
for the likes of me.

09:52.263 --> 09:53.472
For your help.

09:56.726 --> 09:57.977
Sulk all you wish.

09:58.060 --> 09:59.937
I know you'll scoop it up
as soon as I'm gone.

11:41.372 --> 11:42.581
Sorry.

11:49.714 --> 11:51.132
Piss off.

11:51.215 --> 11:52.466
Beg pardon, men.

11:54.343 --> 11:56.470
I wish to speak
to the master of the games.

12:05.396 --> 12:06.397
Oh!

12:07.648 --> 12:08.649
What do you want, man?

12:10.276 --> 12:11.485
Got you again!

12:11.569 --> 12:14.029
I came for the tourney.

12:15.197 --> 12:17.992
My lord's tourney
is a contest for knights.

12:18.075 --> 12:19.452
-You a knight?
-Hyah!

12:19.535 --> 12:21.579
Oi! Psst!

12:25.708 --> 12:27.042
A knight with a name, mayhaps?

12:28.627 --> 12:29.628
Dunk.

12:31.172 --> 12:32.298
Ser Dunk.

12:33.674 --> 12:37.470
I was squire to Ser Arlan of Pennytree
since I was a boy.

12:38.554 --> 12:41.766
He knighted me before he passed,
with his own sword.

12:45.895 --> 12:48.063
That's his penny there in the hilt.

12:50.483 --> 12:52.985
Well, a sword it is for a certainty.

12:54.195 --> 12:56.071
But I've never heard
of this Arlan of Pennytree.

12:56.155 --> 12:57.448
You were his squire, you say?

12:57.531 --> 12:59.950
He always meant for me
to be a knight one day...

13:01.118 --> 13:02.161
as he was.

13:03.162 --> 13:04.872
Am I to be a knight one day, ser?

13:05.915 --> 13:07.082
As you are?

13:12.338 --> 13:15.049
When he was dying,
he called for his longsword

13:15.132 --> 13:16.383
and bade me kneel.

13:17.718 --> 13:19.220
Charged me to be a good knight.

13:20.137 --> 13:22.014
To defend the weak and the innocent.

13:23.557 --> 13:27.061
Serve the realm with all my might.
And I swore that I would.

13:32.650 --> 13:35.027
Any knight can make a knight, it's true.

13:35.110 --> 13:38.280
Were there witnesses to your dubbing?

13:38.864 --> 13:40.741
Only a robin in a thorn tree.

13:44.620 --> 13:46.247
This is Ashford town, lad.

13:47.581 --> 13:50.501
Know what comes to men here
who pretend at sacred oaths?

13:51.085 --> 13:52.711
-I'm not--
-We hang you

13:52.795 --> 13:55.297
naked by your hands and your feet...

13:56.298 --> 13:59.718
lower you down asshole first
onto a sharpened point

13:59.802 --> 14:01.303
and fuck you dry.

14:02.096 --> 14:05.307
Call it the Ashford chair.
So, I ask you again.

14:05.391 --> 14:08.727
Were there witnesses to your dubbing
besides a fuckin' songbird?

14:10.145 --> 14:13.899
Well, the-- see, it was raining.

14:15.192 --> 14:17.194
I'm bullshitting you.

14:21.740 --> 14:22.992
"Ashford chair."

14:24.034 --> 14:25.452
You take a boot to the head?

14:25.536 --> 14:27.538
This is the Reach, not the Riverlands.

14:27.621 --> 14:29.665
-"Ashford chair."
-Think we're fending off

14:29.748 --> 14:33.168
some scourge of cottagers,
scuttling about, entering tourneys?

14:36.045 --> 14:37.464
You'd need coin.

14:38.340 --> 14:40.384
Armor. Horses. Men.

14:40.467 --> 14:42.344
Training, gods be good.

14:43.053 --> 14:46.640
Imagine the poor farmer charging down
Lyonel Baratheon in the lists.

14:46.724 --> 14:48.142
Mm, that would be--

14:48.225 --> 14:49.685
A different sort of entertainment.

14:49.768 --> 14:52.646
Mm. Well, I'm no farmer.

14:52.730 --> 14:54.273
Yet you've come dressed as one.

14:57.192 --> 15:00.154
Look, man, my Lord Ashford

15:00.237 --> 15:03.532
fancies himself of great import.
Gods know why.

15:03.616 --> 15:05.993
Well, that means I'm to ward off
every landed knight

15:06.076 --> 15:07.828
and sellsword vying to challenge.

15:07.912 --> 15:10.205
You understand? There are princes about.

15:12.082 --> 15:13.292
No, of course.

15:21.800 --> 15:22.927
Your late master.

15:25.638 --> 15:27.765
He'll be known to the true knights
here assembled?

15:28.891 --> 15:32.937
There was a pavilion
flying the banner of House Dondarrion.

15:33.020 --> 15:34.855
Aye, Ser Manfred of that house.

15:34.939 --> 15:37.942
Ser Arlan served
his lord father in Dorne a few years past.

15:38.025 --> 15:39.610
Ser Manfred will remember us.

15:39.693 --> 15:41.904
By scent alone, no doubt.

15:41.987 --> 15:44.448
If he'll speak to your good honor,
bring him here with you

15:44.531 --> 15:45.991
before the tourney begins on the morrow.

15:46.075 --> 15:47.117
Leave your escorts behind.

15:48.661 --> 15:50.287
-As you say.
-Aye.

15:53.123 --> 15:55.751
You are aware that those
vanquished in tourney

15:55.834 --> 15:59.380
forfeit their arms, armor, and horse
to the victors, and must ransom them back?

15:59.463 --> 16:01.423
-Aye.
-And you have coin

16:01.507 --> 16:03.926
-to pay such ransom?
-Oh, gods, no.

16:04.802 --> 16:07.721
I mean, I won't have need of coin.

16:11.558 --> 16:12.559
Ah!

16:12.851 --> 16:14.019
Seven fu--

16:35.416 --> 16:37.334
Mind those two. Good girl.

16:42.715 --> 16:45.259
Pardon, sers.
I need speak with Ser Manfred.

16:45.342 --> 16:46.468
Good.

16:46.552 --> 16:49.596
He's napping, ser. Wake him for a stag.

16:50.389 --> 16:51.515
I...

16:52.850 --> 16:54.351
I don't have a stag.

16:54.435 --> 16:56.395
What kind of knight don't got a stag?

16:56.478 --> 16:58.772
-It's a hedge knight, ain't it?
-What?

16:58.856 --> 17:01.025
It's like a knight, but sadder.

17:01.108 --> 17:02.651
No, I'm-- I'm not sad--

17:02.735 --> 17:04.945
He's gotta sleep in the hedges
'cause no lord'll have it.

17:05.028 --> 17:07.238
Aw. That is sad.

17:07.989 --> 17:10.117
And Ser Manfred's fucked its wife, too.

17:10.199 --> 17:13.161
-No, I don't have a wife.
-Oh!

17:13.245 --> 17:15.122
'Cause we're used
to husbands coming 'round.

17:15.205 --> 17:16.748
Likes fucking wives, that one.

17:16.832 --> 17:18.499
Near as much as he likes fucking us.

17:18.584 --> 17:21.420
Told me he's on a mission
to turn the whole world red.

17:21.503 --> 17:24.381
-Well, we're already red.
-So we are.

17:27.051 --> 17:31.513
Well, when do you expect
Ser Manfred to wake, then?

17:32.473 --> 17:34.683
It might wanna try back at evenfall.

17:34.767 --> 17:36.143
Evenfall.

17:39.188 --> 17:40.439
-Goodbye.
-Yeah.

17:41.982 --> 17:43.275
Arse.

17:48.989 --> 17:50.449
Why'd she say that, huh?

17:52.534 --> 17:53.702
We're not sad.

17:57.164 --> 17:59.792
Certainly not
rising-to-the-level-of-a-comment sad.

18:01.210 --> 18:03.462
Besides, Ser Arlan always said that...

18:04.630 --> 18:06.882
a hedge knight
was the truest kind of knight.

18:08.884 --> 18:11.678
When we win our first tilt,
we'll have the loser's armor

18:11.762 --> 18:13.972
and horse, or his gold.

18:14.681 --> 18:15.933
Won't be sad then.

18:22.856 --> 18:25.484
I know. Said if we did win.

18:27.069 --> 18:30.114
Look, it's not a crime against the king
to enjoy a nice thought for a trice.

18:32.741 --> 18:34.743
Do not muck about with me, Raymun.

18:35.911 --> 18:38.038
You're a good-for-nothing useless rat.

18:49.174 --> 18:50.926
What are you gawping at,
you blue-eyed cunt?

18:54.138 --> 18:55.806
That's a longsword you wear?

18:58.559 --> 18:59.977
Yes, it is mine by right.

19:00.561 --> 19:02.062
That's an odd thing to say.

19:05.190 --> 19:08.318
I'm Ser Steffon Fossoway.
Come try me.

19:09.403 --> 19:11.905
As you see,
me cousin here is not ripe yet.

19:11.989 --> 19:13.657
Do it, ser.

19:13.740 --> 19:16.535
I may not be ripe,
but my cousin's rotten to the core.

19:16.618 --> 19:18.328
-Knock the seeds out of him.
-Quiet!

19:21.290 --> 19:24.418
I thank you,
but I have matters to attend.

19:24.501 --> 19:26.879
What, matters of the hedge,
I have no doubt.

19:29.381 --> 19:31.300
Fucking size of ya.

19:31.383 --> 19:34.511
Stupid bastard. Ser Grance!

19:40.475 --> 19:42.853
Perhaps we should seek
quieter accommodations.

20:32.402 --> 20:34.529
Oh. Fuck.

20:50.671 --> 20:52.005
He's napping still.

20:53.048 --> 20:54.508
-Still?
-Mm.

20:54.591 --> 20:56.885
On account of his gouty toes.

20:58.512 --> 21:02.307
One of life's absurd little miseries,
to be sure.

21:04.142 --> 21:06.895
Makes for restless nights.
The poor dear.

21:06.979 --> 21:08.730
Right, absolutely. It's just...

21:08.814 --> 21:10.857
Well, it is of some urgency
that I speak with him,

21:10.941 --> 21:13.819
so I may enter the lists on the morrow.

21:15.028 --> 21:18.031
-What's this?
-It means the joust.

21:18.115 --> 21:19.658
Awful dangerous, that.

21:19.741 --> 21:20.993
Yes, well...

21:22.035 --> 21:24.705
I'm not troubled with
a wealth of options, am I?

21:25.831 --> 21:27.374
And if I mean
to take service in a castle--

21:27.457 --> 21:30.335
It must put its body at hazard
for the pleasure of strangers.

21:30.419 --> 21:31.586
Ain't that our job?

21:31.670 --> 21:35.215
Ah! Shut up!
You're meant to be dead.

21:36.842 --> 21:39.511
Find a safer trade, lad.
You'll be happier for it.

21:40.220 --> 21:41.930
One whore to another.

21:46.518 --> 21:47.894
Must you mock me?

21:48.854 --> 21:50.397
I was only asking for a bit of help.

21:51.481 --> 21:53.567
I'll try Ser Manfred back in the morning.

21:55.444 --> 21:56.528
Sorry, lad.

21:57.112 --> 21:59.323
Aye. We don't mean to mock you.

21:59.406 --> 22:02.492
We see plenty of green boys every tourney.

22:02.576 --> 22:05.245
All with glory in their minds,
but never in their hands.

22:05.829 --> 22:08.332
Well, perhaps I will be different.

22:10.751 --> 22:14.880
Be good to your body, knight.
Last one you're like to have.

22:23.263 --> 22:27.768
Our brave hero forges on,
leaving all he knows behind.

22:28.852 --> 22:33.190
A father and a friend,
may seem the world unkind.

22:34.691 --> 22:38.737
Fate has set his lonely path
through corridors of chance.

22:39.696 --> 22:44.493
A boy from nothing risks it all,
ignoring looks askance.

22:44.576 --> 22:49.331
Perhaps he's only stupid
holding fast his mirror shield.

22:50.082 --> 22:55.253
Great honor his ambition,
must keep a truth concealed.

22:55.337 --> 22:59.883
For if his humble shape is bared,
a foul and fiery demise.

23:00.384 --> 23:04.888
Should the dragon discover
none but a man in great disguise.

23:39.589 --> 23:41.591
Halfman! Halfman!

23:43.468 --> 23:45.220
Do I look like a half man to you?

23:45.303 --> 23:48.014
Aye. Half man, half giant.

23:48.098 --> 23:49.558
Look, I'm sorry.

23:49.641 --> 23:51.685
I should not have urged you
to try my cousin.

23:51.768 --> 23:55.021
He'd have broken your hand
or a knee, if he could.

23:55.105 --> 23:56.940
He likes to batter men in the yard,

23:57.023 --> 23:59.067
you know, in case
he meets them in the lists.

24:00.986 --> 24:02.404
He did not break you.

24:03.155 --> 24:04.281
I'm his blood.

24:04.906 --> 24:06.992
Though he is the senior branch
of the apple tree,

24:07.075 --> 24:08.743
which he never ceases to remind me.

24:10.495 --> 24:12.831
Will you and your cousin
ride in the tourney?

24:12.914 --> 24:17.085
He will. I would that I could,
but I'm only a squire.

24:21.131 --> 24:22.757
Fight well for a squire.

24:24.217 --> 24:27.888
You have the look of a challenger.
Whose shield do you mean to strike?

24:30.724 --> 24:32.476
Makes no difference.

24:32.559 --> 24:34.311
That's what you're supposed to say.

24:39.191 --> 24:41.276
Though it makes
all the difference in the world.

24:44.488 --> 24:45.489
You hungry?

24:46.865 --> 24:47.991
Always.

25:12.098 --> 25:15.018
Lyonel Baratheon.
The Laughing Storm, they call him.

25:16.937 --> 25:18.396
I thought he'd be bigger.

25:18.480 --> 25:20.732
Four thousand years ago...

25:21.983 --> 25:24.110
-Four thousand years...
-Where are you going?

25:24.194 --> 25:27.447
...ago-- cunts. I can't hear myself.

25:28.073 --> 25:32.494
I've had a profound thought,
if anyone would care to listen.

25:36.289 --> 25:38.625
Four thousand years ago,

25:38.708 --> 25:44.339
our ancestors gathered
in that big field outside

25:44.422 --> 25:48.843
to blood each other with sticks
and have a little bit of gay fun.

25:48.927 --> 25:52.472
And they say it was
this country's first-ever joust.

25:52.556 --> 25:54.099
Well, I say...

26:00.939 --> 26:01.940
The fuck was I gonna say?

26:02.023 --> 26:03.942
"First-ever joust..."

26:05.569 --> 26:06.570
Ah.

26:09.656 --> 26:12.826
Men could not have devised such a joy.

26:15.870 --> 26:16.955
So, who was it?

26:20.625 --> 26:21.668
Huh?

26:22.711 --> 26:23.753
Who was it?

26:34.389 --> 26:37.934
Fuck it. A hundred gold to the man,
beast, or god who sticks me best.

26:39.477 --> 26:42.939
Now, eat your birds so we can dance!

27:44.751 --> 27:47.962
You ever been punched in the face before?

27:50.173 --> 27:51.841
I beg your pardon, Ser Lyonel?

27:51.925 --> 27:55.720
Big men get punched more than little men.
Did you know that?

27:57.681 --> 27:59.974
No, but I believe it.

28:02.686 --> 28:05.814
That why you slouch?
So you don't get punched?

28:05.897 --> 28:08.191
I don't slouch.

28:08.274 --> 28:12.821
Oh, you've been cowering all evening
like a maiden on her wedding night.

28:14.781 --> 28:18.118
I meant no disrespect, ser, honest.

28:18.201 --> 28:21.788
Where I grew up,
you learn to go unnoticed, is all.

28:22.664 --> 28:24.457
The seven above gave you tallness.

28:25.458 --> 28:26.710
So, be tall.

28:28.128 --> 28:30.880
Or I will name you a heretic and burn you.

28:31.965 --> 28:35.760
Drown you. Drop you off a tall pl--

28:35.844 --> 28:37.679
I don't know.
What do they do to heretics?

28:37.762 --> 28:40.223
Burn them, my lord.

28:40.306 --> 28:41.349
Fine.

28:42.058 --> 28:43.601
What have you brought me?

28:49.357 --> 28:53.737
Ser, I-- beggin' your pardons.
I didn't realize.

28:54.946 --> 28:56.990
You wish to curry my favor some.

28:58.450 --> 29:00.076
Yet you come with an empty hand.

29:04.664 --> 29:06.040
Lord Cafferen,

29:06.124 --> 29:07.959
the smug cunt in red...

29:09.461 --> 29:11.546
he is scarce to pay his rents.

29:11.629 --> 29:16.092
His people starve each winter,
yet even he shinied up this...

29:17.510 --> 29:19.345
bauble from his family's cellars,

29:19.429 --> 29:22.348
for he understands
that all men, in their way,

29:22.432 --> 29:25.935
wish only for your help, or your head.

29:28.897 --> 29:30.523
You've come for my head, then.

29:32.108 --> 29:33.651
What?

29:33.735 --> 29:36.070
No! No.

29:36.571 --> 29:40.408
Then, why the fuck are you in my tent?

29:45.163 --> 29:46.664
Supper.

29:59.677 --> 30:00.720
Alright.

30:02.889 --> 30:04.516
Actually makes sense.

30:05.058 --> 30:06.935
-Supper.
-What is your name, man?

30:08.770 --> 30:10.021
Dunk-- Ser Dunk.

30:10.104 --> 30:11.481
That's ridiculous.

30:16.653 --> 30:17.946
Do you like dancing?

30:18.029 --> 30:19.989
Doesn't everyone?

30:21.407 --> 30:24.369
Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

31:45.909 --> 31:49.412
The swells heaved.
You could lick salt from the air.

31:51.122 --> 31:54.292
But I'd come to find what men do
when they die at sea.

31:56.044 --> 31:59.047
So, drove I on into the storm.

32:03.718 --> 32:06.471
-Weren't you afraid?
-Ahh.

32:09.933 --> 32:11.976
Within every man, there are many men.

32:13.770 --> 32:15.188
Mm.

32:15.271 --> 32:18.942
But that I had to do,
Stormlanders had always done.

32:19.025 --> 32:22.070
And if they had done it,
I could do it, too.

32:23.279 --> 32:24.280
Hm.

32:25.198 --> 32:27.033
You know, it's best not to agonize.

32:30.411 --> 32:33.414
Yeah, I agonize a lot.

32:34.415 --> 32:35.708
Mm.

32:35.792 --> 32:38.795
Sometimes, I think I agonize too much,

32:38.878 --> 32:41.339
and I just end up agonizing over that.

32:42.382 --> 32:43.716
Mm.

32:44.801 --> 32:46.886
I'm quick and strong, sure.

32:46.970 --> 32:49.514
-Sure.
-But so are you.

32:49.597 --> 32:50.598
Sure.

32:50.682 --> 32:53.101
Plus, you've trained sword and lance

32:53.184 --> 32:55.520
with the finest masters-at-arms
in the realm.

32:55.603 --> 32:56.688
I mean...

32:57.730 --> 33:00.650
what chance do I have? Truly?

33:01.818 --> 33:03.152
Oh, you have no chance.

33:09.867 --> 33:14.163
But it's a great honor to test oneself
against a worthy foe.

33:16.457 --> 33:19.293
-No disrespect, ser.
-Mm.

33:19.377 --> 33:20.837
That's easy for you to say.

33:20.920 --> 33:24.340
You have a name, an inheritance.

33:24.424 --> 33:28.219
One loss, and I won't be able
to ransom back my own horse.

33:35.268 --> 33:37.520
A knight without a horse
is no knight at all.

33:38.396 --> 33:40.398
-Aye.
-Mm.

33:43.985 --> 33:45.194
So, what should I do?

33:49.699 --> 33:51.117
I don't know.

33:53.995 --> 33:55.705
I'm really quite drunk.

34:04.130 --> 34:05.131
Okay.

34:06.215 --> 34:07.216
Thanks.

34:11.262 --> 34:12.137
Sorry.

34:34.035 --> 34:35.619
Ser Arlan of Pennytree.

34:36.746 --> 34:38.706
He served your Lord Father

34:38.789 --> 34:40.833
to hunt the Vulture King
in the Red Mountains.

34:41.626 --> 34:42.751
I was only a boy, but--

34:42.835 --> 34:44.336
I thought you said you were a Dornishman.

34:45.421 --> 34:47.673
No, he said he's hung like a Dornishman.

34:47.757 --> 34:50.425
No, I said I've hung Dornishmen.

34:52.929 --> 34:54.680
Perhaps we would speak on the morn.

34:54.764 --> 34:56.432
I know your penny knight not.

34:56.516 --> 34:58.976
Nor you, brother. Be gone.

35:03.147 --> 35:06.192
But Ser Arlan took a wound
in your father's service.

35:06.275 --> 35:07.610
How could you have forgotten him?

35:10.613 --> 35:13.825
My lord father took 800 swords
into those mountains.

35:13.908 --> 35:17.161
We've forgotten men
who reaped much more than a wound.

35:17.954 --> 35:20.832
Please, ser,
I will not be allowed to challenge

35:20.915 --> 35:23.376
unless a knight
or a lord will vouch for me.

35:23.626 --> 35:24.627
And what is that to me?

35:51.028 --> 35:52.155
You!

35:53.656 --> 35:54.657
What...

35:56.993 --> 35:58.244
What are you doing?

35:58.327 --> 36:01.122
Cooking a fish. Do you want some?

36:01.205 --> 36:05.918
No! I mean, how did you get here?
Did you steal a horse?

36:06.002 --> 36:07.753
I rode in the back of a lamb cart.

36:09.005 --> 36:10.089
Lamb cart.

36:11.716 --> 36:14.135
-Well, you best find another one.
-You can't make me go.

36:14.218 --> 36:16.012
I'd had enough of that inn.

36:16.095 --> 36:19.473
Now, listen, I'll have no more
insolence from you, boy.

36:19.557 --> 36:22.185
I should throw you over my horse
and take you home.

36:22.268 --> 36:24.729
You'd need to ride all the way
to King's Landing.

36:24.812 --> 36:27.273
-You'd miss the tourney.
-King's Landing?

36:28.274 --> 36:30.193
-You're from Flea Bottom?
-No.

36:31.944 --> 36:32.945
Aye.

36:40.620 --> 36:42.038
What are those doing there?

36:42.121 --> 36:43.539
I washed them.

36:43.623 --> 36:46.584
I made the fire, caught the fish,
and groomed the horses.

36:46.667 --> 36:49.837
I would have raised your pavilion,
but I couldn't find one.

36:51.047 --> 36:53.341
-There's my pavilion.
-That's a tree.

36:53.424 --> 36:56.010
Yes, and it's all the pavilion
a true knight needs.

36:57.011 --> 36:59.889
I'd sooner sleep under the stars
than in some smoky tent.

37:01.557 --> 37:02.850
What if it rains?

37:03.476 --> 37:05.228
The tree will shelter me.

37:05.311 --> 37:06.395
Trees leak.

37:09.023 --> 37:10.608
So they do.

37:10.691 --> 37:11.943
What's your name?

37:13.110 --> 37:15.529
-Dunk.
-Ser Dunk.

37:15.613 --> 37:18.950
That's no name for a knight.
Is it short for Duncan?

37:19.784 --> 37:21.911
Yeah. Yes.

37:21.994 --> 37:23.704
Ser Duncan of...

37:29.710 --> 37:31.170
Ser Duncan the Tall.

37:32.129 --> 37:33.714
Never heard of him.

37:33.798 --> 37:35.675
Do you know every knight
in the Seven Kingdoms, then?

37:35.758 --> 37:37.134
The good ones.

37:40.012 --> 37:42.390
-You got a name, thief?
-Egg.

37:42.473 --> 37:43.474
Egg.

37:45.184 --> 37:48.938
Well, Egg, by rights,
I should beat you bloody,

37:49.021 --> 37:50.314
send you on your way.

37:52.108 --> 37:53.901
But you look as though you don't eat much.

37:55.278 --> 37:57.405
And if you'll swear
to do as you're told...

37:59.657 --> 38:01.158
I'll let you serve me for the tourney.

38:04.036 --> 38:05.162
After that, well...

38:07.665 --> 38:08.749
we'll see.

38:11.627 --> 38:15.298
I don't have much,
but if you prove worth your keep...

38:16.924 --> 38:19.260
you'll have clothes on your back
and food in your belly.

38:20.469 --> 38:22.805
The clothes might be
rough-spun and the food,

38:22.888 --> 38:24.890
salt beef and salt fish,

38:24.974 --> 38:26.225
but you won't go hungry.

38:28.144 --> 38:29.770
I promise not to beat you.

38:31.063 --> 38:32.648
Except when you deserve it.

38:33.649 --> 38:34.692
Yes, my lord.

38:36.360 --> 38:37.361
"Ser."

38:39.238 --> 38:40.656
I'm only a hedge knight.

38:53.419 --> 38:55.921
A falling star brings luck
to those who see it.

38:58.341 --> 39:00.217
Go to sleep, boy.

39:00.301 --> 39:03.387
All the other knights
are in their pavilions by now,

39:03.471 --> 39:05.890
staring up at silk instead of sky.

39:08.059 --> 39:09.685
Do you want a clout in the ear?

39:20.738 --> 39:22.823
So, the luck is ours alone?
